            <title>[JDK-8307653] Adjust delay time and gc log argument in TestAbortOnVMOperationTimeout</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8307653</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently, `TestAbortOnVMOperationTimeout` always fails on &lt;br/&gt;
my local riscv64 dev board because of the poor performance of the board,&lt;br/&gt;
and it fails on macos-aarch64 intermittently (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8296819&quot; title=&quot;runtime/Safepoint/TestAbortOnVMOperationTimeout.java fails with &amp;#39;exitValue = 1&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8296819&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8296819&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
So I want to increase the delay time so that the test can pass at my local riscv64 env,&lt;br/&gt;
and adjust the gc log argument to inspect the issue about macos-aarch64.</description>
